content.text:
The issue was that when importing settings (e.g. from K-9 Mail), special folder assignments (Sent, Drafts, Trash, Spam, Archive) were not being correctly preserved if the import specified `AUTOMATIC` selection (or if it defaulted to `AUTOMATIC` in newer versions) even when a specific folder name was provided. This caused Thunderbird to attempt auto-detection, ignoring the imported folder name, which often led to incorrect or missing assignments.

To resolve this, I modified `legacy/core/src/main/java/com/fsck/k9/preferences/SettingsImporter.kt`. I added a post-processing step `fixSpecialFolderSelection` in the `importAccount` method. This step checks if a specific folder name (e.g., `sentFolderName`) is present in the imported settings. If it is present and the corresponding selection mode (e.g., `sentFolderSelection`) is set to `AUTOMATIC`, it forces the selection mode to `MANUAL`. This ensures that the imported folder name is respected and used, effectively preserving the assignments from the exported settings.

The changes involve:
1.  Importing `app.k9mail.legacy.account.Account.SpecialFolderSelection`.
2.  Calling `fixSpecialFolderSelection(currentAccount)` after the account settings upgrade and before writing the account to storage.
3.  Implementing `fixSpecialFolderSelection` to iterate over special folders and apply the fix.

This ensures that users migrating from K-9 Mail or restoring settings will have their folder assignments correctly preserved.

```kotlin
// legacy/core/src/main/java/com/fsck/k9/preferences/SettingsImporter.kt

// ... imports ...
import app.k9mail.legacy.account.Account.SpecialFolderSelection

// ... inside importAccount ...
        var currentAccount = accountSettingsUpgrader.upgrade(contentVersion, validatedAccount)
        currentAccount = fixSpecialFolderSelection(currentAccount)

        val accountMapping = accountSettingsWriter.write(currentAccount)
// ...

// ... helper method ...
    private fun fixSpecialFolderSelection(account: ValidatedSettings.Account): ValidatedSettings.Account {
        val settings = account.settings.toMutableMap()
        var changed = false

        val folders = listOf("archive", "drafts", "sent", "spam", "trash")

        for (folder in folders) {
            val nameKey = "${folder}FolderName"
            val selectionKey = "${folder}FolderSelection"

            val folderName = settings[nameKey] as? String
            val selection = settings[selectionKey] as? SpecialFolderSelection

            if (folderName != null && selection == SpecialFolderSelection.AUTOMATIC) {
                settings[selectionKey] = SpecialFolderSelection.MANUAL
                changed = true
            }
        }

        return if (changed) {
            account.copy(settings = settings)
        } else {
            account
        }
    }
```

